ES5 Global Constants
const PI = 3.14;
PI = 42; <-- this will throw an error

What is the difference between VAR and LET? 
  Var can be reassigned and redeclared. Let cannot be redeclared. Additionally, let cannot be hoisted and creates a block scope.
  
What is the difference between VAR and CONST?
  Var can be reassigned and redeclared, CONST cannot. Const is not hoisted, and it creates a block scope.
  
What is the difference between LET and CONST?
  Let can be reassigned, but const cannot.

What is hoisting?
  Hoisting is when variables are lifted or hoisted to the top of the scope they are declared in - this only works with var.
